    ],
    "notes": "Primary detection signal is Sysmon EID 2 (FileCreateTimeChanged) where process.executable resolves outside trusted directories (System32, Program Files, SysWOW64). Chaining EID 1 → EID 2 on the same PID within seconds is high-confidence for Fawkes timestomp. Key differentiators from benign: (1) executable path under AppData/Temp vs. system/installed paths; (2) affected file.extension is exe or dll rather than documents; (3) no recognizable backup/archive parent command_line pattern. Blue team rule should alert on EID 2 where process.executable matches *\\AppData\\* OR *\\Temp\\* OR *\\ProgramData\\* and file.extension in (exe, dll, bat, ps1)."
  },
